which is contradictory to (24), since Un(·) is the utility function based on coalition order. Therefore, for G, given coalition order and Un(·) as the preference relation and utility function, there exists at least one stable coalition partition , i.e., the convergence of G is guaranteed. Notably, the potential function φ prefers the total ranging utility, which guarantees that each player’s local utility is involved in the total utility. Hence, the stable coalition partition turns to be the optimal solution of problem P.
IV. COOPERATIVE LOCALIZATION SCHEME DESIGN BASED ON CFG
After constructing and analyzing the stability of the CFG model, this section designs the coalition formation algorithm based on rules given in Section III-D. Further, it builds the cooperative localization scheme based on CFG to perform the clustering-based UAV swarm cooperative localization. The specific flowchart of the scheme is shown in Fig. 3, and each block diagram with a corresponding section.
A. Algorithm Design of CFG Model
Based on the analysis of the stable coalition partition in Section III, this section is introduced to design an algorithm for the proposed CFG model G. The above preference relations and formation rules will be applied in the algorithm design. However, due to the diversity of strategy sets, this kind of optimal selection approach often falls into the trap loop, that is, local optimum.
Fig. 3. Cooperative localization scheme design based on CFG.
Motivated by the log-linear learning algorithm designed in [40] and [41], we construct the UAV coalition/FL-BDs/SLBDs selection algorithm based on coalition order (CSA-CO Algorithm), as shown in Algorithm 1. The algorithm’s core is to follow the coalition selection mechanism; according to Theorem 1, it can converge P in the solution of the problem. Here, β is the learning parameter (β > 0). The convergence of the log-linear learning algorithm has been proven in [42]. Given the designed utility function, the algorithm can effectively converge to the NE point. By adjusting β, the proposed algorithm can compromise between exploration and selection, which guarantees the effect of convergence and improves the speed of convergence. According to the proposed algorithm, given two coalitions, says COcn and COck , after executing coalition form
ing/breaking, COc∗n and COc∗k are obtained, then the update probability function is given as follows:
Prob( (j + 1) = (j)))
= exp{β · U(sn, s−n)}
exp{β · U(sn, s−n)} + exp{β · U(sn∗, s−n
)} (28)
Prob( (j + 1) = ∗) = 1 − P( (j + 1) = (j)). (29)
U(sn, s−n) = V(COcn , ) + V(COck , ), U(sn∗, s−n) =
V(COc∗n , ∗) + V(COc∗k , ∗), which are designed based on coalition order. Besides, Algorithm 2 is designed for FLBDs/SL-BDs selection while coalition selection is determined. This algorithm adopts the best response to complete FL-BDs/SL-BDs selection based on coalition value to obtain the optimal solution.
