B. DS-TWR-Based Time Slot Design
The operation scheme of DS-TWR is shown in Fig. 4. For instance, in the 4-node network, take UAV 1 as the tag, then UAV 2, UAV 3, and UAV 4 are anchors. The network only needs five measurement frames (sending two frames and receiving three frames) to locate the label and complete the ranging exchange. The propagation time between UAV 1 and UAV k ∈ {2, 3, 4} is calculated as follows:
τ1,k = τR1A × τRkA − τP1A × τPkA
